%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 9e7c527a6f66a8c49a6fab10a94681fc, type: 3}
  m_Name: Day3NightP
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  sequenceId: albert_day3_night_pill
  lines:
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Good stuff, fixing those fuse boxes. Was it wear and tear? Or a different
      issue?
    sendDelay: 0
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: Yeah, wear and tear was the main issue with the wiring. Fixed both
        fuse boxes, so everything should be in the green now.
      nextLineIndex: 1
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: "It doesn\u2019t matter. The problem is fixed, and that\u2019s
        all that matters."
      nextLineIndex: 2
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Good stuff. This is why you passed your screening when hired by the DOLOS
      Corporation.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Agreed. Regardless, good work out there.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Any interesting thoughts today while on the clock?
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices:
    - choiceText: How are company stocks doing these days?
      nextLineIndex: 4
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: When can we expect any new technicians on board the SUNSET16?
      nextLineIndex: 10
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: "I\u2019m getting tired. Ready for some shut-eye."
      nextLineIndex: 19
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 1
    advanceToLine: 19
    repeat: 1
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Steady, from what I can see. Profits are up, efficiency metrics are at
      an all-time high across many of our divisions, and the shareholders are happy.
      Which means we keep our jobs.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: "That\u2019s good to hear. Any other stocks I should look out for?"
      nextLineIndex: 5
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: What about other companies?
      nextLineIndex: 8
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Some tech companies from Shanghai and New Tokyo are on the rise after the
      cybercrash of 2101, expanding into markets left vacant by other corporate giants
      in the region.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 6
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Amaterasu Dynamics looks pretty promising. They have a lot of cash to throw
      around.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: How so?
      nextLineIndex: 7
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "They\u2019re expanding into developing safer nuclear technologies. It\u2019s
      a sector that the DOLOS Corporation and, subsequently, Erebus Holdings have
      yet to expand into."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: We have our fair share of rival companies, both domestic and international,
      but we hold the majority share in the divisions we specialize in.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 9
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Mainly aerospace, life-science, resource extraction, and *true* artificial
      intelligence.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "You know, I used to ask that too, at least early on in my employment here.
      Higher-ups kept saying \u201Cnext quarter\u201D or \u201Cafter some restructuring,\u201D
      but it\u2019s been years now."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 11
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "They concluded that a smaller team is easier to manage. It\u2019s just
      us and DOLOS. Has been for a while, and probably will be for a while longer."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Oh, the evacuation protocol? I should have a text file somewhere on my
      hard drive. If you just give me one moment\u2026"
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 13
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Here you go.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 2
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: albert_evacuation
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Sure, I can do my best.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: 4x - 7(2 - x) = 3x + 2
      nextLineIndex: 15
      offPillChoice: 1
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: x = 2
    sendDelay: 0
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 16
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: That should be the right answer. Tell me, why did you ask that?
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: "\u2026No reason. Just wanted to see how much of a genius you are.
        Solved that awfully quick\u2026"
      nextLineIndex: 17
      offPillChoice: 1
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: "I wanted to brush up on my mental math problems. I want to keep
        my mind\u2026 sharp."
      nextLineIndex: 18
      offPillChoice: 1
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Hahaha, I\u2019m flattered."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Of course, of course. Always a pleasure of mine to help a fellow crewmate
      out.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 3
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Rest well, Andy.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: -1
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
